author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúI work for the people on the streets. I don‚Äôt work for the federation, not for the government. I don‚Äôt care if they‚Äôre happy with me or not. The most important thing is to make the people happy.‚Äù

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúIn the beginning, it was also difficult for them [the players] to be outside of the list. But, I brought everyone and spoke to them about why I removed them and why I kept them showing them their stats and videos.‚Äù

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
"Some of the players came to my room and hugged me, thanking me for defending them.  The rules are simple: I take the blame for losing, and the players take the credits for all the wins. I work for the players. They must be comfortable, not me."

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúWe don‚Äôt have power for the players here. This hurts me so much. When we lost 6-2 against Iraq, I posted an apology because it was my first match and asked everyone not to blame the players but me." 

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúI called every federation in Asia saying I wanted to play against them. Karma dai and Madhu dai supported me.‚Äù

Almutairi praised ANFA President for arranging the charter flight to Iraq at 2 a.m. "that made Nepal's participation in the #WCQ possible" 

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúThis is the first time, in 50 years, that we‚Äôve played in every FIFA international window. We‚Äôve played 15/16, matches against 7/8 national teams. I challenge any coach before me if they have managed to achieve that in this period of time.‚Äù

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúIt becomes a big problem if it rains, because we do not have the right shoes. We lost two matches because it was raining. When it started raining in the SAFF Cup final against India, you saw our players. It looked like skating, everyone fell down.‚Äù 

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
Almutairi later insisted the government should allow dual nationality to increase the quality of the squad with players that play outside of Nepal and are eligible to represent under FIFA's rules, citing examples of Bangladesh and Indonesia. 

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúIf I had the option, I‚Äôd stay here forever. What Nepal has given to me, I have not given back to Nepal. But the problem is, I want to be in the Asia Cup as a coach. With Nepal, it will be difficult, but we will try.‚Äù 

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúIn 50 years of football in Nepal, there has been no achievement. [The team] has not reached the Asia Cup once or has won 3-4 matches in the qualifiers. Now you want a change ‚Äì it‚Äôs not easy. Some people think it‚Äôs like snapping their fingers.‚Äù 

#Nepal #Football

author: Sudesh
text:
‚ÄúThe problem is not only in the field. I can fix any problem inside the field but outside the field sometimes you face something that you cannot fix.‚Äù 

#Nepal #Football
